{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e2af74e3-1814-4509-8b83-f73486f787e7","content":"In .NET MAUI, lifecycle management moved from `Application` to `Window`. Override `CreateWindow` and hook into window lifecycle events:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = new Window(new AppShell());\n\n    window.Created += (s, e) => { /* OnStart equivalent */ };\n    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* OnSleep equivalent */ };\n    window.Resumed += (s, e) => { /* OnResume equivalent */ };\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\nAlternatively, subclass `Window` and override `OnCreated()`, `OnStopped()`, and `OnResumed()`.\n\nFor platform-specific lifecycle events, use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android.OnStop(activity => { /* ... */ }));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios.DidEnterBackground(app => { /* ... */ }));\n#endif\n});\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"37f3ee4e-044b-45a4-91cd-7ad859999ae8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle methods from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a straightforward knowledge question about the MAUI lifecycle API.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart`, `OnSleep`, and `OnResume` in your `Application` subclass.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the lifecycle model changed. You use the `Window` lifecycle events or the cross-platform lifecycle events through the `ILifecycleBuilder` in `MauiProgram.cs`, or you can override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to window events.\n\nSpecifically, in MAUI:\n\n\n- `OnStart` maps to `Window.Created` or platform-specific lifecycle configuration\n- `OnSleep` corresponds to `Window.Deactivated` or `Window.Backgrounding`\n- `OnResume` maps to `Window.Activated` or `Window.Resumed`\n\nThe key difference is that MAUI shifted from application-level lifecycle to window-based lifecycle. You can override `CreateWindow` to return a `Window` instance with event handlers attached, or configure lifecycle events through the window's event system.","outputTokens":687,"requestId":"9814:23E21D:1648D34:18DE65A:6A051F32"},"id":"e82bc4e0-7507-4c11-8844-ea689abae47f","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:02:55.120Z","parentId":"99d9a06c-c361-4747-b43c-ba75f152389b"}
